      <section id="privacy">
        <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p class="muted">This Privacy Policy explains how Quickbill AI collects, uses, and protects your data. By using the app, you agree to this policy.</p>

        <div class="card">
          <h3>1. Data We Collect</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Account info:</strong> Email address and optional display name (to help you manage invoices).</li>
            <li><strong>Invoice data:</strong> Client names, item descriptions, amounts, and invoice history — stored if you choose to save invoices.</li>
            <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> Non-identifying analytics to improve app performance.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>2. How We Use Data</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Provide core app functionality (create, store, send invoices).</li>
            <li>Offer support and respond to user requests.</li>
            <li>Improve the app via aggregated usage analytics.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>3. Data Sharing &amp; Security</h3>
          <p>We do not sell or share your personal data with third parties for marketing. Data is stored securely and access is limited to authorized personnel.</p>

          <h3>4. Your Choices</h3>
          <p>You can request data deletion or export by contacting us at <a href="mailto:quickbillai.help@gmail.com">quickbillai.help@gmail.com</a>. If you choose not to store invoice data in cloud sync, your invoices will remain local to the device.</p>

          <h3>5. Contact</h3>
          <p>For privacy-related questions: <a href="mailto:quickbillai.help@gmail.com">quickbillai.help@gmail.com</a></p>

          <p class="muted">Last updated: <!-- to be updated when publishing --> <time datetime="2025-10-15">2025-10-15</time></p>
        </div>
      </section>

